The paper focuses on the analysis of pilot reuse in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of stochastic geometry to model the system also suggests a possible category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the benefits of pilot reuse on cell-throughput and user-rate, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and game theory (cs.GT) in terms of optimizing system performance.
